description:
For easy listening, I took the AJ broadcast where he talks about serotonin reuptake inhibitors, put it in Audacity, and edited out the non-relevant parts, and took the relevant and important parts and put them in new .mp3 files.

I also did my best to write down everything being said, in WordPad, and saved it as .rtf's.. so, if you want to; it's possible to read it... or read while listening...

Or whatever ^_^

--------
---
--

Note: Part 3 and 4 connects directly to eachother. I split that segment into two separate files anyway, for some reason (don't really remember why exactly).

There may be other Parts that also connect to eachother, directly, 
or almost directly - can't remember - but, most had several minutes 
of unrelated stuff in between them, sometimes over 10 minutes of audio...
